collection.title: United Way of Dane County

highlights.description: Frank recalls being a 17-yr-old high school senior, straight A student, on a track scholarship, who suddenly drops out of school in December and no one reaches out to ask why. In March, gets locked up, spends the next 20 years of his life in prison.
Michelle says her cousin did 3 years in solitary confinement and then released into the public and he has not recovered.
Frank talks about monetizing bodies through prison gerrymanders.
Mou talks about encountering racism for the first time, here in Madison when someone called her a "gook" on State Street.
Racial slur experienced in Madison + police response
Frank, a returning citizen in Madison, WI, talks about prisons making money off of bodies.
